The responsive version of confluence is pretty good EXCEPT that it lacks a home button! Isn't it funny how sometimes we miss the very basic essential needs....

h3. Summary
missing comma in mobile_whitelist.json and the following error is thrown in the Confluence log file:
{code}
[ThreadPoolAsyncTaskExecutor::Thread 22] [client.eventfilter.whitelist.AnalyticsWhitelistModuleDescriptor] readPluginWhitelist Failed to read whitelist resource file [whitelist/mobile_whitelist.json] in plugin [com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-mobile] due to: [Unexpected character ('"' (code 34)): was expecting comma to separate OBJECT entries
at [Source: java.util.zip.ZipFile$ZipFileInflaterInputStream@54ed6736; line: 8, column: 4]]
{code}

We just upgraded our test server from confluence 5.8.5 to 5.8.9 and LDAP authentication immediately failed and we started getting the following error when trying to test the ldap connection from within confluence (hostname and IP changed below for security):

{code}
Test basic connection : Failed
our.internal.hostname.com:3269; nested exception is javax.naming.CommunicationException: our.internal.hostname.com:3269 [Root exception is javax.net.ssl.SSLHandshakeException: java.security.cert.CertificateException: No subject alternative names matching IP address ##.##.##.## found]
{code}

Our certificate has a field as follows but is lacking the "SUBJECT" field.
{code}
  X509v3 Subject Alternative Name: critical
  DNS:our.internal.hostname.com
{code}

We do not list the IP address anywhere within the certificate either.

Previous versions of Confluence worked fine and this certificate also works on JIRA "v6.4.9#64024-sha1:1f1084e".

I face exactly the same error that is already described in CONF-13582, but with a rather current version:

{quote}
{noformat}| Functional\ Specs: | [space:Page Name]- continuing text{noformat}
becomes
{noformat}| Functional\ Specs: | [Page Name]- continuing text{noformat}
each time I re-open the page for editing. This causes a red link to suggest creating a new page in the current space. If I change the link back to {noformat}[space:Page Name]{noformat} in wiki markup, it will properly reference the link to its correct space, but it is lost on the next page edit. This is highly annoying.
{quote}

