Since we currently have 7 JIRA instances connected to our Confluence, our 150.000 users wish to have the possibility to define a preset for a certain JIRA instance in their User settings. Not all users use the primary instance. Each instance has its own circle of users.

Therefore, a preset per user for a certain JIRA instance would enable users to create or find issues much easier!

In the documentation:
https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Configuring+a+MySQL+Datasource+in+Apache+Tomcat

The suggested dialect needs to be :
{code}
<property name="hibernate.dialect"><![CDATA[com.atlassian.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect]]></property>
{code}
instead of 
{code}
<property name="hibernate.dialect"><![CDATA[net.sf.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect]]></property>
{code}
As it can cause the unknown dialect error when access AO table.

